5. My Reflection about Using AI for Data Analysis

The process was surprisingly easy. However, I noticed two interesting points:

  • when cursor checked the data it selected 2015 data, the last complete year for educational parity, even though I asked it to select 2022. If I was not watching this carefully I might have missed that cursor chose to select a different year than I asked.
  • cursor incorrectly interpreted the maps, stating in both maps that the darker colours were the higher values - it was actually the other way around. My main reflection is that it is important to carefully review the output from cursor and check all the outputs carefully.
